<br>
I have also been interrupted while casting a draught by a Felwithe guard.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
I think alot of it has to do with the level of the spell you are casting more than anything else.  I haven't found that being on a horse, or on my new Drogmor has made any difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 3:54:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26151.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.burleehost.com/moyguild/avitars/sorceress.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drogmor/Horse and Interrupts</span><hr size=1> Is there any more of a benefit (other than the head of the beast being smaller and more out of the way) to getting a drogmor over a horse?  I've been trying to decide what to do in that area.<br>
<br>
And I barely have 2k hp.  I'm pretty much dead if I take that kind of damage.  I've noticed the same thing with interrupts.  Sometimes I get no interrupt and the spell goes fine and sometimes I get no interrupt and at the end of the evac spell it tells me that it didn't go off.  You'd think that it could stop rather than wasting all that time going to the end and then saying it's interrupted. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hikamindsong>Hika Mindsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 4:21:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26151.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> drog vs horse</span><hr size=1> I don't know why horses would help you with channeling.  <br>
<br>
However, drogmor heads get in the way much much less than a horse.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, drogmor do NOT have what can be described as &quot;a smooth gait&quot;.  Riding one of them in real life would be much akin to riding a bull in a rodeo.  <br>
<br>
-- Hika<br>
